> [@TheWhiteBug](https://github.com/TheWhiteBug) is there any chance you could do a `git bisect` to narrow down which change from v1.69.0 to the current beta fixes the problem? If we can work that out then we can put that in v1.69.1 which is due fairly soon.

@TheWhiteBug is talking about this fix: https://github.com/rclone/rclone/commit/2341934d8ee396649745b266050f48b725a100de which is on a dev branch, not `master`. 

It is not quite ready for merging yet as it needs some cleanup and I also wanted to add a test (ironically, recreating this issue will be harder than fixing it!)
